# Caboodle Layout System

When creating or editing HTML in Caboodle, follow these rules:

## Use the layout primitives

The layout system in `styles/layouts.css` provides these composition classes:
`stack`, `box`, `center`, `cluster`, `with-sidebar`/`sidebar`/`not-sidebar`, `switcher`, `cover`/`cover-centered`, `grid`, `frame`, `reel`, `imposter`, `icon`/`with-icon`, `container`.

Before writing new layout CSS, check whether an existing primitive (or a combination of primitives) solves the problem. Compose layouts by nesting: e.g. `.center .stack` for a centered, vertically-spaced column.

## Configure with custom properties, not new classes

Each primitive exposes CSS custom properties (`--space`, `--min`, `--threshold`, `--sidebar-width`, etc.). Set these inline or via a scoping class rather than creating one-off layout rules.

```html
<!-- Good: configure via custom property -->
<div class="grid" style="--min: 18rem; --space: var(--s2)">

<!-- Avoid: one-off class that reimplements grid behavior -->
<div class="my-custom-grid">
```

## Common compositions

| Content type | Recommended layout |
|---|---|
| Introductory hero | `.cover .center` → `.cover-centered .stack` |
| Body text | `.center .stack .prose` |
| Card collection | `.center .stack` → `.grid` (children: `.card`) |
| Sidebar navigation | `.center .with-sidebar` |
| Feature comparison | `.center .switcher` |
| Tag / filter bar | `.cluster` |
| Horizontal showcase | `.reel` |

## Spacing rules

- Use the modular scale tokens (`--s-5` through `--s5`) from `tokens.css` for all spacing.
- Never use magic-number pixel values for margins, padding, or gaps.
- Prefer logical properties (`margin-block-start`, `padding-inline`) over physical directions.

## No fixed breakpoints for layout

- Do not use `@media (max-width: …)` to rearrange layout. The intrinsic primitives (Sidebar, Switcher, Grid) handle responsive behavior through container-aware flex/grid math.
- `@media` is acceptable for non-layout concerns (e.g., adjusting font size, hiding decorative elements).

## Page structure

Follow the page shell from `docs/requirements/caboodle-page-blueprint.md`:
- `<body class="page">` wraps `<header class="page-header">`, `<main>`, `<footer class="page-footer">`
- Each content block is a `<section class="section">` containing a `.center` wrapper
- Use `.stack` for vertical rhythm inside sections
- Use `.prose` on text-heavy containers

## Migration safety

- Keep class names semantic and stable — they will map to framework components later.
- Do not tie layout rules to specific HTML element types (e.g., avoid `section.stack`; prefer `.stack`).
- Keep all tokens in `tokens.css` so they can be extracted to a framework theme config.

